  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The ProCore ultrasound biopsy needle, used primarily to obtain intra-abdominal tissue core
      biopsies, has not been widely used for endobronchial ultrasound-guided transbronchial needle
      aspiration (EBUS-TBNA). In this study the investigators are going to evaluate the utility of
      the ProCore needle for sampling mediastinal or hilar lymph nodes during EBUS-TBNA versus
      standard 22 gauge needle for diagnosis of lung cancer.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
